repo.name: cython

body:
Most of the time the pre-calculated hashes will already be different and we don't need to compare the strings.

This gets the `kwargs2` benchmark in #6683 down from
```
f1: 31.21866300352849 ms
f2: 41.543947998434305 ms
f3: 52.85455100238323 ms
```
to
```
f1: 17.570152995176613 ms
f2: 18.495469994377345 ms
f3: 19.021035986952484 ms
```

Closes https://github.com/cython/cython/issues/6683

comment_data.body:
May I suggest also introducing the hash test here as well ?
Since the hash tests doesn't need a function call, I would also suggest to place it before the length test (same comment for the other place).
The length test is a macro and doesn't need a function call either. But yes, the hash seems more likely to mismatch than the length.
In principle there's an unhandled error I think (although a fairly unlikely one).
Would it more readable to make this stuff the definition of `__Pyx_UnicodeKeywordsEqual` when not `CYTHON_USE_UNICODE_INTERNALS`

```suggestion
        // Not found after keyword args, check for (unlikely) duplicate positional argument.
```
I think?
I'm not sure. I meant "the argument name was not found in the (keyword) argument names that follow the positional arguments". Clearly not a good comment.
Currently, `__Pyx_UnicodeKeywordsEqual` cannot fail and doesn't need error handling. `PyUnicode_Compare` can fail.

commit.message:
Avoid calling PyUnicode_Compare() when validating keyword arguments.
Most of the time the precalculated hashes will already be different.

Closes https://github.com/cython/cython/issues/6683
Refactor to move hash test before length test because it tends to be more selective.
Remove the length check after the hash check since it will almost always succeed there.
Add separate implementation for dict-to-dict copying case with **kwargs.
Use PyUnicode_RichCompare() instead of PyUnicode_Compare() since it appears to have a tiny speed advantage.
Use low-level Unicode string comparison in CPython.
Fix loop.
Only check for duplicate positional arguments if not all kwargs could be matched to keyword parameters.
Avoid creating **kwargs dict and *args tuple if their user space variable is unused.
Fix accidental code duplication.
Special-case the "dict + dict" case in "__Pyx_MergeKeywords()".
Remove unused function argument.
Stick to setting unused **kwargs to NULL and exclude *args since it crashes in PyPy (and is thus probably not safe as is).
Add comment.
Add error handling to "__Pyx_MergeKeywords" and avoid the critical section and dict iteration if there is nothing to do.
Always use "PyArg_ValidateKeywordArguments()" to validate the keywords dict.
Add error handling to PyDict_Size() call.

Remove dedicated switch-based keyword unpacking code and replace it with a generic implementation that runs over the keyword tuple/dict.

This is actually faster for the vectorcall protocol and probably not slower for the (now rarely used) keyword dict calls. It also saves a lot of special per-function C code.

Closes https://github.com/cython/cython/issues/6688
Explicitly reject keyword arguments in functions that do not allow them.
Reorder code for better grouping.
Wrap long lines.
Specialise also the "no/unused **kwargs" case for calls with a keyword dict.
Fix bugs in non-CPython code sections.
Fix C conversion warning.
Fix critical section exit.
Fix fast path for comparison against known keyword arguments in "__Pyx_RejectUnknownKeywords()".
Avoid useless loop code generation.
Code cleanup for better readability.

milestone.description:
* Remove code for Python 2 and Python < 3.8.
* Integrate better with Python 3.
* Improve support for the Limited API.
* Start supporting GIL-free Python 3.13.
* Support the Py3.13 `sys.monitoring` API.
* Support and use `am_send` for coroutines.

title: Reduce overhead when validating keyword arguments
